    <note>Yang(2) Yungong [2037] A member of a wealthy Sichuan lineage that entered government service and sustained official status through military administration at the time of the pacification of Sichuan. Ke's [2015] and Gao's [2018] father. Jiangxi TZ, 9.8a-8b; XCB, 34.15b (n.), 40.8b, 12a, 42.1a; LPJ, 18.1b; SS, 309.7a-8a. Identification as a Zhongshan Yang(2) and address suggest that Yungong's lineal ancestor was Yang(2) Ke [4047], who moved here from Changan at the end of the Tang.</note>
